'''Joshua Benjamin Brenet''' (born 20 March 1994) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[full-back (association football)|full-back]] for [[Kayserispor]]. Born in the Netherlands, he plays for the [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao national team]].<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |title=Joshua Brenet Stats {{!}} Soccerway |url=https://www.soccerway.com/player/brenet-joshua/AiIfuEh9/ |access-date=2025-11-24 |website=www.soccerway.com |language=en}}</ref>

==Club career==

=== PSV ===
Brenet is a graduate of PSV's youth academy, having joined the club in 2011 from [[A.V.V. Zeeburgia|Zeeburgia]]. He made his professional debut on 6 December 2012 in a [[UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] game against [[S.S.C. Napoli|Napoli]], coming on for [[Peter van Ooijen]] after 87 minutes.<ref>[https://www.worldfootball.net/match-report/ma1552282/lineup/ Match details / line-up: SSC Napoli - PSV Eindhoven (Europa League 2012/2013)<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
He made his Champions League qualification debut on 30 July 2013 against [[S.V. Zulte Waregem|Zulte Waregem]].

In November 2015, Brenet's contract with the club was extended until summer 2017,<ref>{{Cite web |date=6 November 2015 |title=Brenet verlengt contract bij PSV tot medio 2017 |url=https://www.nu.nl/sport/4160159/brenet-verlengt-contract-bij-psv-tot-medio-2017.html |access-date=25 February 2026 |website=NU.nl |language=nl}}</ref> and in December 2016, his contract with the club was again extended until summer 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |date=21 December 2016 |title=Brenet verlengt PSV-contract tot medio 2020 |url=https://www.ad.nl/nederlands-voetbal/brenet-verlengt-psv-contract-tot-medio-2020~a35472b4/ |access-date=25 February 2026 |website=Algemeen Dagblad |language=nl}}</ref>

He played on 15 April 2018 as PSV beat rivals Ajax 3–0 to clinch the [[2017–18 Eredivisie]] title.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/43776657|title=PSV Eindhoven 3-0 Ajax|work=BBC Sport}}</ref>

=== TSG Hoffenheim ===
On 24 May 2018, it was announced that Brenet had signed for [[Bundesliga]] club [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|TSG Hoffenheim]] on a four-year contract, for a fee rumoured to be €3,500,000.<ref>{{Cite web |date=24 May 2018 |title="Hochinteressante Alternative": Brenet kommt zur TSG |url=https://www.kicker.de/hochinteressante-alternative_brenet-kommt-zur-tsg-724536/artikel |access-date=2026-02-25 |website=kicker |language=de-DE}}</ref> Though he made 14 Bundesliga appearances in his [[2018–19 TSG 1899 Hoffenheim season|debut season at the club]] under manager [[Julian Nagelsmann]], he did not play in the Bundesliga at all in the first half of the [[2019–20 TSG 1899 Hoffenheim season|2019–20 season]] under new manager [[Alfred Schreuder]],<ref>{{Cite web |date=27 December 2019 |title=Brenet steckt in der Sackgasse |url=https://www.kicker.de/brenet_steckt_in_der_sackgasse-766054/artikel |access-date=2026-02-25 |website=kicker |language=de-DE}}</ref> and on 31 January 2020, he joined [[SBV Vitesse]] on loan until the end of the season.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Lammers |first=Lex |date=31 January 2020 |title=Vitesse slaat toe op de transfermarkt: club huurt Joshua Brenet van Hoffenheim |url=https://www.ad.nl/transfer-talk/vitesse-slaat-toe-op-de-transfermarkt-club-huurt-joshua-brenet-van-hoffenheim~ad285683/ |access-date=25 February 2026 |website=Algemeen Dagblad |publisher=DPG Media |language=nl}}</ref> He played 4 times for the club prior to the suspension of their season due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic in the Netherlands|COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=26 March 2020 |title=Hoffenheims Winterabgänge: So geht es Vogt, Brenet und Co. |url=https://www.kicker.de/hoffenheims_winterabgaenge_so_geht_es_vogt_brenet_und_co_-772856/artikel |access-date=2026-02-25 |website=kicker |language=de-DE}}</ref>

Brenet made just one Bundesliga appearance during the [[2020–21 TSG 1899 Hoffenheim season|2020–21 season]], as a late substitute in the first match of the season,<ref>{{Cite web |last=Pfeifer |first=Michael |date=13 May 2021 |title=Hoeneß sortiert Brenet aus |url=https://www.kicker.de/hoeness-sortiert-brenet-aus-804809/artikel |access-date=2026-02-25 |website=kicker |language=de-DE}}</ref> and he was moved to the club's [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim II|reserve team]] for the 2021–22 season,<ref>{{Cite web |last=Pfeifer |first=Michael |date=25 August 2021 |title=Ohne Perspektive: Kann sich Brenet bei Hoffenheims U 23 empfehlen? |url=https://www.kicker.de/ohne-perspektive-kann-sich-brenet-bei-hoffenheims-u-23-empfehlen-869397/artikel |access-date=2026-02-25 |website=kicker |language=de-DE}}</ref> for whom he made 10 appearances in the [[Regionalliga Südwest]], and scored one goal.<ref name=":2">{{Kicker season|id=joshua-brenet|season=2021-22|access-date=25 February 2026}}</ref>

=== Twente ===
On 31 January 2022, Brenet joined [[FC Twente|Twente]] until the end of the 2021–22 season.<ref>{{cite press release|publisher=[[FC Twente|Twente]]|url=https://www.fctwente.nl/nieuws/joshua-brenet-komt-naar-fc-twente/|title=Joshua Brenet komt naar FC Twente|date=31 January 2022|access-date=4 February 2022|language=nl}}</ref> In July 2022, he signed a new two-year contract with the club, turning down a contract offer from [[Feyenoord]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Inan |first=Johan |date=7 July 2022 |title=Joshua Brenet verkiest zekerheid bij FC Twente boven veel beter salaris bij Feyenoord |url=https://www.tubantia.nl/sport/joshua-brenet-verkiest-zekerheid-bij-fc-twente-boven-veel-beter-salaris-bij-feyenoord~a4be0bf6/ |access-date=25 February 2026 |website=Tubantia |publisher=DPG Media |language=nl}}</ref>

=== Later career ===
Brenet signed for [[Al-Rayyan SC]] in September 2024. His only appearances came in the [[AFC Champions League Elite]] as he was not registered by the club to play in the domestic league.  He left the club in June 2025.<ref>{{cite press release|publisher=Twente Insite|url=https://www.twenteinsite.nl/oud-spelers-fc-twente/brenet-verlaat-al-rayyan-ziyech-kort-na-komst-in-qatar-ook-alweer-clubloos?comment=156230|title=Brenet leaves Al-Rayyan, Ziyech also without a club shortly after arriving in Qatar|date=2 June 2025|language=nl}}</ref>

In September 2025, Brenet was linked with a move to Scottish side [[Livingston F.C.|Livingston]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Daily Record|url=https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/football-transfer-news/livingston-target-ambitious-transfer-swoop-35992240|title=Livingston target ambitious transfer swoop for ex Netherlands cap with free agent in Scotland|date=30 September 2025}}</ref> He signed for Livi on 1 October 2025 until July 2026.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Livingston FC|url=https://livingstonfc.co.uk/squad-update-joshua-brenet-joins-the-lions/|title=Joshua Brenet joins the Lions|date=1 October 2025}}</ref> During his four-month stay with ''The Lions'', the team failed to win a game, and Brenet announced on his Instagram page that he had signed for [[Kayserispor]] on 6 February.<ref>{{cite web |title=Joshua Brenet - Kayserispor |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/DUasjLiCAiR/ |website=Instagram |access-date=6 February 2026}}</ref> This was later confirmed by Livingston, saying he "exercised his option to depart the club" for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web |title=Squad Update {{!}} Brenet moves on |url=https://livingstonfc.co.uk/squad-update-brenet-moves-on/ |website=Livingston FC |access-date=6 February 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in the Netherlands, Brenet is of Curaçaoan descent. Brenet made his debut for the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] in a November 2016 [[friendly match]] against [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]].<ref>[http://www.ad.nl/dossier-wk-voetbal/oranje-debuut-psv-ers-brenet-en-ramselaar~aa34f12b/ Oranje-debuut PSV'ers Brenet en Ramselaar] - AD {{in lang|nl}}</ref> He was called up to the preliminary squad for the [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao national team]] for the [[2021 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].<ref name=":0">{{cite web|date=18 June 2021|title=2021 Concacaf Gold Cup preliminary rosters announced|url=https://www.concacaf.com/gold-cup/article/2021-concacaf-gold-cup-preliminary-rosters-announced/|access-date=19 June 2021|publisher=CONCACAF}}</ref>

Brenet made his [[List of association footballers who have been capped for two senior national teams|debut]] for [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao]] on 5 June 2024 in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – CONCACAF second round|2026 World Cup qualification]] match starting against [[Barbados national football team|Barbados]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/698142|title=2026 World Cup Qualifying - Concacaf, Second Round|website=ESPN.com|date=5 June 2024|language=|access-date=6 June 2024}}</ref>

==Personal life==
In March 2024, he was sentenced to a month in prison for [[Driver's license|driving without a license]] on two occasions. His contract with Twente expired at the end of the 2023–24 season and was not extended.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=NOS|url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2514395-brenet-speelt-niet-meer-voor-fc-twente-na-veroordeling-tot-celstraf|title=Brenet speelt niet meer voor FC Twente na veroordeling tot celstraf|trans-title=Brenet no longer plays for FC Twente after prison sentence|date=27 March 2024|language=nl}}</ref>

